(21307, 4283, '_title', 'field_5a5e2fd6ce55f'),
(21308, 4283, 'description', 'Anthony Rini was appointed vice president for finance in August 2017. He is responsible for the development and support of integrated, long-range financial, operational, and capital planning. He also oversees business services operations, including procurement services, parking, dining, the bookstore, mail services, and leased properties. Rini joined Northeastern in 2011 as vice provost for budget, planning, and administration. During his time in the Office of the Provost, he led the effort to implement a decentralized budget model. Rini holds a Master of Public Administration from the University at Albany, SUNY, and a doctoral degree in education from the University of Pennsylvania.'),
